
[1]gratulate

   GRAT'ULATE, v.t. [L. gratulor, from gratus, pleasing, grateful.]

   1. To express joy or pleasure to a person, on account of his success,
   or the reception of some good; to salute with declarations of joy; to
   congratulate. [The latter word is more generally used.]

   To gratulate the gentle princes there.

   2. To wish or express joy to.

   3. To declare joy for; to mention with joy.
